#  Novel Hub

A modern Netflix-style Single Page Application (SPA) for discovering, saving, and exploring books using the Open Library API.

---

##  Overview

Novel Hub is a frontend web application that allows users to:

*  Search for books in real time
*  View detailed book information
*  Save favorite books
*  Explore books in a Netflix-style layout
*  Listen to book titles using text-to-speech
*

---

## Purpose

This app is designed to help users:

> Discover new books, organize their reading list, and explore book details — all in a smooth, interactive interface.

---

## Features

### Book Search

* Fetches data from Open Library API
* Displays title, author, and cover

###  Featured Banner

* Highlights a selected book
* Dynamic background and actions

###  Favorites Section

* Save books to localStorage
* View your personal library
* Persistent across sessions

### Read Section (SPA View)

* Displays selected book details
* Includes title, author, and cover


###  Text-to-Speech

* Listen to book titles


###  Responsive Design

* Works across different screen sizes

---

##  How It Works (SPA Architecture)

This project follows a Single Page Application approach:

* No page reloads
* Sections are toggled using JavaScript
* Views include:

  * Home
  * Favorites
  * Read

---

## Technologies Used

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript (Vanilla JS)
* Open Library API

---

##  API Used

### Open Library API

Provides book data including:

* Titles
* Authors
* Covers
* Book identifiers

